岗位职责:
Job Title: Officer/Assistant Officer (UG Teaching &amp; Learning Support)
Department: College of Educational Sciences (CES), VPTLO, HKUST (GZ)
Job Posting Details
Formally established in June 2022, the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (Guangzhou)(HKUST(GZ)) is a cooperatively-run university between the Chinese mainland and the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. HKUST(GZ) has obtained approval from the Ministry of Education (MoE) and become the first legally-independent educational institution co-established by the Mainland and Hong Kong since the announcement and implementation of the “Outline Development Plan for the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area” and the “Overall Plan for Deepening Globally Oriented Comprehensive Co-operation amongst Guangdong, Hong Kong and Macao in Nansha of Guangzhou”. With a spirit of pioneering innovation, HKUST(GZ) charts new territories in cross-disciplinary education and explores new frontiers in pedagogies, aiming to serve as a role model of the mainland-Hong Kong integrated educational development and become a world-famous high-level university, endeavoring to nurture future-oriented, high-level and innovative talents. 
In response to the increasingly complex challenges faced by the rapidly changing world, HKUST(GZ) adopts a brand-new and cross-disciplinary academic structure featuring “Hub” and “Thrust” to substitute the conventional one characterized by “school” and “department”, facilitating cross-disciplinary integration while vigorously developing emerging and frontier disciplines. This is a groundbreaking move in the higher education community across the globe.
HKUST(GZ) comprises four Hubs, namely Function Hub, Information Hub, Systems Hub, Society Hub and 16 thrusts. The admission of undergraduate students begins in 2023, with the first batch of programs covering artificial intelligence, data science and big data technology and smart manufacturing engineering.
HKUST(GZ) is located at *** Duxue Road, Qingsheng Hub Cluster, Nansha District, Guangzhou. The campus covers an area of about 1,669 mu (111.3 hectares) and is divided into two construction phases. The first phase covers an area of about 716 mu (47.7 hectares) with a floorage of about 636,000 square meters (63.6 hectares), which had been officially put into use in September 2022. The design of the campus blends natural scenery with architecture, with key cutting-edge technologies for energy conservation and environmental protection adopted during the design and construction process, in a bid to establish the campus as a new benchmark of green, smart and sustainable development.
The College of Education Sciences (CES), under Vice-President for Teaching and Learning, is the academic unit responsible for first and second year undergraduate education, offering humanities, social sciences, language and STEM courses. CES will conduct research in the fields of cognitive sciences and innovative pedagogy. CES also serves as the home unit for UG students before their program major determined, providing students with academic-related services. The College is composed of five divisions, including Division of General Education (DGE), Division of STEM Education (STEM), Division of Cognitive Sciences (DCS), Division of Language Education (DLE), Division of UG Teaching Labs (UGTL).
We are seeking for capable and self-motivated candidates to work as the Officer/Assistant Officer in CES to provide administrative support in undergraduate teaching &amp; learning and assist with the general affairs in the College. The appointee will be stationed in Nansha, Guangzhou.
Duties
The major responsibilities of the appointee include but are not limited to the following: 
1.Work closely with the faculty members and Committees on the development and delivery of UG Common Core and Fundamental courses in the Year 1 and Year 2 undergraduate studies throughout the process from the course design to course evaluation;
2.Work closely with the faculty members and IEIP on the UG Teaching &amp; Learning Innovation, including the development and implementation of UG course modulization and innovative pedagogical practices across the University;
3.Work closely with other departments and offices on the academic affairs of UG students under the remit of CES;
4.Assist with the general affairs in CES including meetings and reports, documentation, reimbursement, logistics, etc.
5.Other ad hoc duties assigned by the supervisor.
任职要求:
Qualification Requirements
1.A Bachelor's degree or above in STEM/Education/Humanities/Social Sciences or related fields;
2.At least 2 years’ working experiences, preferably in administrative positions at higher education sector;
3.Candidates with teaching and learning related experiences (e.g., administrative support on course design and development) are preferable;
4.Excellent multitasking and time management skills, strong self-motivation, and meticulous working habits;
5.A strong team player and active learner with good communication skills, a high sense of responsibility, confidentiality, and able to work under high pressure;
6.A good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
7.High computer proficiency, including knowledge and experience of MS Office.
This is a Mainland appointment, and the appointee will be offered a contract by HKUST(GZ) entity in accordance with the Mainland labor laws and regulations. Starting salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.
HKUST (GZ) is an equal opportunities employer and is committed to our core values of inclusiveness, diversity, and respect.

